From: OpenEmbedded <oe.patch@oe>
Date: Mon, 15 Jun 2020 17:33:57 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 8/8] Tweak LIMA_PMU_SW_DELAY

As suggested in
https://gitlab.freedesktop.org/lima/linux/-/issues/33#note_532492
---
 drivers/gpu/drm/lima/lima_pmu.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/drivers/gpu/drm/lima/lima_pmu.c b/drivers/gpu/drm/lima/lima_pmu.c
index 571f6d661..e547bf4d4 100644
--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/lima/lima_pmu.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/lima/lima_pmu.c
@@ -39,7 +39,7 @@ int lima_pmu_init(struct lima_ip *ip)
 	/* If this value is too low, when in high GPU clk freq,
 	 * GPU will be in unstable state.
 	 */
-	pmu_write(LIMA_PMU_SW_DELAY, 0xffff);
+	pmu_write(LIMA_PMU_SW_DELAY, 0xff);
 
 	/* status reg 1=off 0=on */
 	stat = pmu_read(LIMA_PMU_STATUS);
